Going by his acting prowess in some notable films, Gabriel Afolayan’s portrayal as postal boy of a new thriller is a selling point for the yet to be released movie, Coming from Insanity. Produced by contemporary film and creative art house – The Movement Pro. Pictures – trailer of the company’s debut feature film makes it more striking, ahead of the April 5, 2019 cinema release date. Distributed by FilmOne, Coming from Insanity is a crime drama based on the awe-inspiring true story of “Kossi the Bear”, a notorious currency counterfeiter with genius-level intelligence. The trailer begins with Kossi and his crew enjoying a beautiful day at the beach, before taking us back in time to his childhood and his days as a house boy in Lagos. The trailer then quickly transitions into a web of intricate plots full of suspense and intrigue leaving the audience gasping for more. Written and Directed by Akinyemi Sebastian Akinropo and Produced by Ibidolapo Ajayi, Coming From Insanity boasts award winning performances from a talented ensemble cast led by Gabriel Afolayan, Sani Danja, Dakore Akande, Bolanle Ninalowo, Damilola Adegbite, Wale Ojo, Sharon Ooja, Wole Ojo, Udoka Oyeka, Sambasa Nzeribe, Tina Mba, Odunlade Adekola, Adeolu Adefarasin, Temidayo Akinboro, Ijeoma Aniebo, DJ Izybeatz among others.